This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By Cui Huiying, southern weekly reporter

Editor in chief | Wang Tao

There is only a third-class hospital in the city, a protective clothing wear 8 hours also reluctant to throw away, with plastic film self-made Goggles, buy their own dilution of industrial alcohol..

Medical staff, supplies... everything is missing, this is the Hubei Province "North Gate" Suizhou predicament.

As of 2400 hours on February 5,2020, there were 834 confirmed cases of pneumonia in COVID-19, the youngest prefecture level city in Hubei with 2.58 million people. With 3.2 confirmed cases per 10,000 people, the rate of infection is among the highest in Hubei Province, where one city in Suizhou has more confirmed cases than most other provinces, behind Zhejiang, Guangdong and Henan.

On February 5, Xiaodong Wang, deputy secretary of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee and governor of Hubei Province, came to Suizhou to inspect and direct the prevention and control of the epidemic. According to the official website of the Suizhou government, on the evening of February 5,31 medical teams from the Hubei Provincial Cancer Hospital were sent to Suizhou to assist the 31 medical staff, all from the intensive care medical profession.

1
There are very few medical staff for critical patients

1

###There are very few medical staff for critical patients

There are 12 medical institutions in Suizhou, of which five are designated for the new pneumonia outbreak, but only one is designated as a third-class hospital in central Suizhou. Since January 25, this hospital has issued three public announcements to raise materials.

"The departments of cardiology, gastroenterology and other departments have deployed half of the medical staff to support the infection department, but the medical staff and medical supplies are still not enough, " Su Nan, a general doctor at Suizhou City Center Hospital, told southern weekend.

As of 2400 hours on February 4,2,123 doctors and 925 medical staff had been put on standby, according to data provided by staff at Suizhou's COVID-19 pneumonia control headquarters, but most health care professionals are limited to the average patient, and even then, "one health care worker has to work with several patients, " said Wu Qing, a member of the command's medical care research team.

From the twenty-nine of the 12th month, medical teams from all over the country came to Hubei, but before the 31-member medical team from the Hubei Provincial Cancer Hospital arrived, there were only four people from Inner Mongolia in Suizhou.

The core problem of the lack of medical staff is that there are very few medical staff for critical patients. "doctors and nurses in the ICU need professional knowledge and competence, and we are understaffed in this part of the country, " Wu Qing said. The ability of a hospital to treat critically ill patients will determine whether they live or die.

As of 2400 hours on February 5, there had been nine deaths in Suizhou, according to the provincial health and health commission's website.

In the past, the Infectious Diseases Department of Suizhou City Centre Hospital was only a department, the number of patients can be treated about 100, now a temporary increase of four wards, still inadequate.

Wu Qing said the city currently has the capacity to admit 1,975 confirmed patients, in addition to about 700 confirmed patients are still in hospital, there are at least 404 suspected cases, "Some people with fever, even people with a headache or a cold, feel panic and go to fever clinics and ask to be hospitalized. Beds are far from enough. "

In addition to the shortage of medical staff, beds, protective supplies are also in short supply. At current consumption, Suizhou's central hospitals need about 1,000 protective clothing, 2,000 N95 masks and 8,000 surgical masks per day.

Su Nan, the current critical care and fever clinic medical staff can also get a full set of protective supplies, to save protective clothing, they work a shift of 8 hours, "do not go to the toilet, do not eat and drink. ".

"If we have no choice, we may replace it with a common hat or reuse the protective clothing after disinfection, " said Wang Guangjun, who collects medical supplies at Suizhou's central hospital.

Non-first-line medical staff, a week can only be assigned to an N95 mask. "Some doctors use disposable medical masks outside the N95 mask, only changing one layer, " Su Nan said in a husky voice.

General surgical masks are also in high demand, with prices rising from 1 yuan to 5.5 yuan a piece a few days ago when supplies were at their most tight, "I could only buy a few thousand tablets to meet emergency needs. The Dean said that money should not be considered first, and the hospital should also guarantee the first-line medical staff with the money first. " Wang Guangjun told southern weekend.

To Suran's surprise, bottled medical alcohol has also become so scarce. Now their department has to go to the supplies department with a bucket of water, fetch a few liters of 95% industrial alcohol, water it down to 75% and repackage it.

It's harder for hospitals to get masks these days. Thanks to a public appeal for help, a small donation has been received so far. Wang Guangjun calculated that there are currently 20,000 to 30,000 pieces of general medical masks, which can be used for four to five days.

He has been several days to the City Health Commission reported chlorine-containing rapid hand sanitizer gap, but so far has not been related to the material under the allocation. "normally hospitals don't use this disinfectant, so they don't stock it because it's more effective for coronaviruses, and now you can't buy it. We have people watching and guarding a lot of factories and sometimes it takes two or three days to get some."

On Feb. 3, a company in Shandong donated 20 pieces of instant hand sanitizer, which will last about two days. Wang Guangjun even told southern weekend that as long as they have supplies, they can pick up the goods themselves by car and transport them to the highway junction or even Wuhan.

In addition to the Suizhou City Center hospital, many medical institutions in Suizhou are also actively seeking material donations. "Now basically all the county CDC supplies are distributed to the township, every day supplies, basically the next day empty, " said a CDC staff member in Sui County.

2
First case confirmed in Lunar New Year

2

###First case confirmed in Lunar New Year

The first confirmed case in Suizhou was reported on January 24,2020, on Lunar New Year's Eve. As of 2400 hours on January 24,1,287 cases have been confirmed in China, according to the website of the National Health Commission. On that day, the province's first confirmed cases were not only in Suizhou, but also in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, Ezhou and Tianmen.

In other provinces, counties and even the United States and France have confirmed cases, the first city in Hubei Province confirmed, was called by the media "dark under the lights. ". As of 2400 hours on February 5, the number of confirmed cases in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, Ezhou and Tianmen also reached 144,432 and 138 cases respectively.

On December twenty-eight, she had received a 68 year old woman with chest tightness but no fever. A CT scan showed what looked like viral pneumonia. A throat swab was taken that night and the next morning it tested positive for viral nucleic acid, they were immediately referred to the infection department, where both couples were later diagnosed and treated for complications in the intensive-care unit. "They say they haven't been to Wuhan, but they don't know if they've had any contact with people from Wuhan, " said Su Nan, who said the couple were among the first Suizhou patients to be found.

Also in the New Year's Eve, January 24,24:00, Suizhou began "closed" , but before that has returned to Suizhou many returnees have been sick. After the first case was detected, new cases were confirmed daily in Suizhou from January 25 to 28, with 31,16,18 and 46 cases respectively. In the days after January 30, there were 70 to 80 new cases per day. On February 3, there were 183 new cases.

People's Daily Online reported that two other clusters of infections occurred in Suizhou, both before January 20. People who had been to Suizhou after returning from a trip to Wuhan were not feeling well but were still having meals together. Observation of close contacts revealed that many people had been diagnosed.

Southern weekend reporters checked the Suizhou news section of the Suizhou city government's website and found that there was no news about the outbreak before January 21. On January 1, when the South China Seafood Wholesale Market in Wuhan detected multiple cases, there's no information on that either. Until 9 am on January 22, the website published a Suizhou Daily News Article "January 21, Municipal Party secretary Chen Ruifeng presided over the city Standing Committee meeting" . On January 23, the first meeting of the city's COVID-19 was held.

According to the first press conference in Suizhou, as of 0:00 on January 25, Suizhou has identified five designated treatment hospitals, set up 134 isolation wards, reserved two close contacts, 108 rooms and 198 beds.

The epidemic is getting worse and more people are being infected. As of February 4, the number of beds in Suizhou had increased tenfold from 10 days ago, but they are still stretched to the limit. SUIZHOU's central hospitals have taken turns working overtime to test the nucleic acid, but each batch takes six hours to complete up to 200 cases a day.

Suizhou has also begun to implement quarantine measures, such as Sui County's official announcement that on February 4, the main head of the county's statistics bureau entered households in Zhenjiang Yi village, Tang County, for body temperature registration. Focus on the road control personnel on duty, home temperature monitoring, confirmed cases of close contact with the object row and isolation observation.

On February 4, at the meeting of the Standing Committee of the Municipal Party Committee (enlarged) and the fifth plenary meeting of the municipal COVID-19 epidemic prevention and control headquarters, chaired by Chen Ruifeng, secretary of the Municipal Party Committee, it is suggested that "all residents should be checked for body temperature and all those with fever symptoms should be isolated for medical observation" .

On the morning of Feb. 5, Su said, they have received information that Suizhou City Center Hospital will vacate a 21 story building for patients with viral pneumonia or suspected viral pneumonia. Wu Qing also confirmed to southern weekend reporters that the work has been in the docking since February 4, "the current situation and received feedback from the public phone, the current bed is far from meeting the needs of patients. "

If it works, it will be Suizhou's Little Tangshan model.

Su Nan and Wu Qing were assumed names at the request of the interviewee
